<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 1 — Run the SQL</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open your Supabase dashboard → <strong>SQL Editor</strong> → <strong>New Query</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste the entire <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">.sql</code> file and click <strong>Run</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You'll see all 5 tables created + your 12 stays and 5 sample bookings seeded</li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 2 — Create your admin user</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">In Supabase → <strong>Authentication</strong> → <strong>Users</strong> → <strong>Add User</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Email: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">admin@paharipath.in</code> (or whatever you want)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Set a strong password</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">This replaces the old hardcoded <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">admin/manager</code> credentials — now it's real auth</li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 3 — Open the HTML</h4>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Open <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">PahariPath_supabase.html</code> in your browser. On load it will:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Fetch stays from Supabase (replacing hardcoded array)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Fetch crowd overrides (so your admin edits apply globally)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Show a brief "Loading PahariPath…" toast</li>
</ul>
