-streaming="false" class="group relative relative pb-[var(--msg-assistant-pb,0.75rem)]" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><h2 data-find-omitted="" class="sr-only select-none">Claude responded: Here's your exact order of operations:</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's your exact order of operations:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 1 — Deploy to Netlify (Do this first, today)</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>netlify.com</strong> → Sign up free</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Add new site → Deploy manually</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag and drop <strong>both files</strong> together:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">PahariPath_v4_full.html</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">manifest.json</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Once uploaded, rename <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">PahariPath_v4_full.html</code> to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> — Netlify needs this exact name to serve it as homepage</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">You get a live URL like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">paharipath.netlify.app</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Test it opens correctly in browser</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 2 — Buy your domain</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>hostinger.in</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Search <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">paharipath.in</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Buy it (~₹800/year)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to Netlify → <strong>Site Settings → Domain Management → Add custom domain</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Enter <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">paharipath.in</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Hostinger will show you DNS records to add — Netlify guides you through it step by step</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Wait 1-2 hours → your site is live at <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://paharipath.in</code></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 3 — Fix Supabase allowed URLs</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Supabase dashboard → <strong>Authentication → URL Configuration</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Site URL:</strong> <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://paharipath.in</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Redirect URLs:</strong> add <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://paharipath.in</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Save</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 4 — Create PWA icons</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Take your PahariPath logo (or create one on <strong>canva.com</strong>)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Export as PNG, make two sizes:
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">192×192px → save as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">icon-192.png</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">512×512px → save as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">icon-512.png</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload both to Netlify alongside your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 5 — Setup Plausible Analytics</h3>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>plausible.io</strong> → Start free trial (30 days free, then $9/month or use the free self-hosted version)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add site → enter <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">paharipath.in</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">That's it — the script is already in your HTML, it just needs the domain registered there</li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Step 6 — Add partner_applications table to Supabase</h3>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Run this in Supabase → SQL Editor:</p>
