</span><span>→ Turn-by-turn navigation begins</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Clean, simple, and actually works on mountain roads where our map can't compete.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>For photos — let's use Supabase Storage.</strong> Here's why:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Users are in the mountains with bad internet</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Pasting URLs is clunky on mobile</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Supabase Storage free tier is 1GB — enough for hundreds of POI photos</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">We compress images before upload so they stay small</li>
</ul>
