ont-base">Ran 2 commands, read a file</span><span class="inline-flex -rotate-90 shrink-0 opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-200 group-hover/status:opacity-100 group-focus-visible/status:opacity-100"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Ran 2 commands, read a file</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Done. Here's what changed:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Virtual Tour completely removed</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tab button gone from place detail</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">All JS functions (buildVtour, vtPan, vtZoom) deleted</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">All CSS deleted</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">"Virtual Tour" buttons on place cards now say "📷 Photos" and just open the place detail directly</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>One easy Photos &amp; Videos admin panel</strong> — replaced 3 messy, partially-broken panels with one clean flow:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Admin → Media tab</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select destination</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste Unsplash photo URLs (comma-separated — add 5 at once)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Optionally paste a YouTube URL</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Save Photos &amp; Video</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Saved photos show as thumbnails right there in admin, with a ✕ to remove any</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>How to grab Unsplash URLs:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to unsplash.com → search "Spiti Valley" or whatever destination</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Right-click the photo → <strong>Copy Image Address</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste into the Photo URLs field — repeat for as many as you want, separated by commas</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Save</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Photos instantly appear in the destination's photo gallery on the live site — main image + thumbnail strip, exactly like before, just powered by real photos now.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Upload as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">index.html</code> to GitHub.</p></div></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-2 py-2"><div class="group/artifact-block relative flex text-left font-ui rounded-lg overflow-hidden border-0.5 transition duration-300 w-full hover:bg-bg-000/50 px-4 border-border-300 hover:border-border-200"><button type="button" class="absolute inset-0 cursor-pointer rounded-[inherit] focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-inset focus-visible:ring-accent-200" aria-label="View Paharipath v7"></button><div class="artifact-block-cell flex flex-1 align-start justify-between w-full"><div class="flex flex-1 gap-2 min-w-0"><div class="flex items-end w-[68px] relative shrink-0 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"><div class="absolute right-2 flex flex-1 overflow-hidden w-[52px] h-[71px] rounded-t-lg border-0.5 border-border-200 select-none scale-[1] group-hover/artifact-block:scale-[1.035] -rotate-[0.1rad] group-hover/artifact-block:-rotate-[0.065rad] duration-300 ease-out group-hover/artifact-block:duration-400 group-hover/artifact-block:ease-[cubic-bezier(0,0.9,0.5,1.35)] transition-transform backface-hidden will-change-transform translate-y-[19%] bg-gradient-to-b from-bg-000 to-bg-000/0 pt-4 items-start justify-center h-full"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-500"><path d="M67.84,92.61,25.37,128l42.47,35.39a6,6,0,1,1-7.68,9.22l-48-40a6,6,0,0,1,0-9.22l48-40a6,6,0,0,1,7.68,9.22Zm176,30.78-48-40a6,6,0,1,0-7.68,9.22L230.63,128l-42.47,35.39a6,6,0,1,0,7.68,9.22l48-40a6,6,0,0,0,0-9.22Zm-81.79-89A6,6,0,0,0,154.36,38l-64,176A6,6,0,0,0,94,221.64a6.15,6.15,0,0,0,2,.36,6,6,0,0,0,5.64-3.95l64-176A6,6,0,0,0,162.05,34.36Z"></path></svg></div></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-1 