image.</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's the exact step-by-step for creating <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og-image.jpg</code>:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 1 — Open Canva</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>canva.com</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Sign in (or sign up free)</li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 2 — Create the right size</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create a design</strong> (top right)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Custom size</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Enter: <strong>Width: 1200px, Height: 630px</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Create new design</strong></li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 3 — Add background</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">On the left sidebar, click <strong>Photos</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Search <strong>"Himachal Pradesh mountains"</strong> or <strong>"Spiti Valley"</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click any photo you like → it fills the canvas</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drag the corners to make sure it covers the whole 1200×630 frame</li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 4 — Darken it slightly (so text is readable)</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click on the photo</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Look for <strong>Edit Image</strong> or <strong>Adjust</strong> in the top toolbar</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Lower the <strong>Brightness</strong> slightly, or add a black rectangle with low opacity on top</li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 5 — Add your logo/text</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Text</strong> in left sidebar → <strong>Add a heading</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Type: <strong>PahariPath</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Make it large, white or your forest green color</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add a subheading below: <strong>Discover Real Himachal Pradesh</strong></li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 6 — Download</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Top right → <strong>Share</strong> → <strong>Download</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">File type: <strong>JPG</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Download</strong></li>
</ol>
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Step 7 — Rename and upload</h4>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Rename the downloaded file to exactly: <strong><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og-image.jpg</code></strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to <strong>github.com/Sakshu237/paharipath</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Add file → Upload files</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Drop <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og-image.jpg</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Commit changes</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
