t-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; user-select: none; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 433.3;"></span><span data-cds="Icon" class="absolute inset-0 transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; user-select: none; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 433.3;"></span></span></span></button><div class="flex items-center"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="[content-visibility:auto] [contain-intrinsic-size:auto_400px] px-2 -mx-2 pb-8 -mb-8 print:[content-visibility:visible]"><div data-test-render-count="2"><div class="group" style="height: auto; opacity: 1; transform: none;"><div class="contents"><div data-is-streaming="false" class="group relative relative pb-[var(--msg-assistant-pb,0.75rem)]" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><h2 data-find-omitted="" class="sr-only select-none">Claude responded: Fair — you want something that actually looks premium, not a generic template.</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Fair — you want something that actually looks premium, not a generic template. Here's a sharper version:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h4 class="text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold">Better approach — design it properly</h4>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 1 — Pick the right photo</strong><br>
Don't use a random stock photo. Go to <strong>unsplash.com</strong>, search "Spiti Valley" or "Himachal mountains snow" — pick something moody and cinematic, not touristy-bright. Look for photos with negative space (sky, empty mountain side) where text can sit naturally.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 2 — In Canva</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Custom size 1200×630</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Paste your chosen photo as full background</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Add a <strong>subtle gradient overlay</strong> — not flat black, a gradient from transparent (top) to dark (bottom-left where your text sits). Canva → Elements → search "gradient" → pick a black-to-transparent one, place over photo, set blend mode to Multiply</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 3 — Typography that doesn't look templated</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Don't use Canva's default heading font</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Search fonts: <strong>Fraunces</strong> or <strong>Playfair Display</strong> for "PahariPath" (serif, editorial feel — matches travel/heritage branding)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Pair with <strong>DM Sans</strong> or <strong>Inter</strong> for the subtext (clean sans-serif)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Keep text bottom-left aligned, not centered — centered text on OG images looks amateur</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 4 — The actual copy</strong><br>
Instead of generic "Discover Real Himachal Pradesh" try something with more edge:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">"146 places Google Maps won't show you"</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">"Go where the crowd isn't"</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">"Real Pahar. Real People. Real Path."</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 5 — Add a tiny badge/tag</strong><br>
Small pill-shaped element top-left: "Live Crowd Data · 146 Destinations" — gives it a product feel, not just a travel blog feel</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">If you want, send me the photo you pick and exact wording you like, and I can describe the precise layout (positions, sizes, colors using your site's palette <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded-[4px] flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(26, 61, 43);"></span>#1a3d2b</code> pine green) so it actually matches the rest of PahariPath's visual identity instead of looking like a separate Canva template.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_3vk_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn